%% Diagram: Flink-style two-phase commit sink lifecycle (begin / preCommit / commit / abort)
%% Type: sequence
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant JM as JobManager (coordinator)
    participant Op as Stream operator
    participant Sink as TwoPhaseCommitSink
    participant Ext as External system\n(Kafka txn / DB)

    Note over JM,Ext: Phase 0 - new checkpoint epoch
    JM->>Op: inject checkpoint barrier N
    Op->>Sink: process records for epoch N
    Sink->>Ext: beginTransaction(txnId=N)

    Note over JM,Ext: Phase 1 - PREPARE
    Op->>Sink: snapshotState(N)
    Sink->>Ext: flush + preCommit (txn open, not visible)
    Sink-->>JM: ack barrier N\n(stores txnId in checkpoint)

    alt all operators ack barrier N
        Note over JM,Ext: Phase 2 - COMMIT
        JM->>Sink: notifyCheckpointComplete(N)
        Sink->>Ext: commit(txnId=N)
        Note right of Ext: Records become visible to\nread_committed consumers.
    else any operator fails to ack
        Note over JM,Ext: Phase 2 - ABORT
        JM->>Sink: checkpoint N failed
        Sink->>Ext: abort(txnId=N)
        Note right of Ext: Pre-committed records\ndiscarded; replay from\nlast committed checkpoint.
    end
